A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 4, 2025, as Oxford Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, founded in 1836 as Emory College, Oxford College has a long and
3 distinguished history that reflects its deep connection to the Methodist Church and its integral
4 role within the broader Emory University community; and
5 WHEREAS, the college transitioned to its current designation as Oxford College in 1964,
6 becoming a two-year liberal arts institution dedicated to providing a rigorous academic
7 foundation for its students; and
8 WHEREAS, located in Oxford, Georgia, Oxford College offers students a unique educational
9 experience that combines the benefits of a close-knit campus environment with the vast
10 resources of a world-renowned research university; and
11 WHEREAS, Oxford College plays a vital role in the Newton County economy, contributing
12 more than $80 million annually, attracting over 12,000 visitors, and supporting over 520
13 local jobs and 1,500 jobs statewide; and
