14 WHEREAS, students at Oxford College are deeply engaged in community service,
15 partnering with more than 65 local organizations, nonprofits, civic groups, and educational
16 institutions to contribute over 13,000 volunteer hours each year; and
17 WHEREAS, Oxford College has remained steadfast in its commitment to academic
18 excellence, fostering an environment where students benefit from close faculty interactions,
19 personalized learning experiences, and a strong sense of community; and
20 WHEREAS, the college has upheld a tradition of intellectual growth, resilience, and service,
21 shaping students who not only excel academically but also develop socially and personally
22 through meaningful engagement with their peers and the wider world; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this distinguished academic institution
24 be appropriately honored during this special time.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize March 4, 2025, as Oxford Day at the state capitol and commend Oxford College
27 for its rich history, academic excellence, and ongoing contributions to Newton County, the
28 State of Georgia, and beyond.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Oxford College.
